;Mozilla’s Key Internet Issues
Ruk'u'x taq runa'oj Ruk'amaya'l Mozilla


;Shaping the Agenda
Rub'anik ri cholb'äl q'ij


;Mozilla has identified five issues that we believe must be tackled in the current era, to build the open internet we want:
Mozilla ruya'on retal wo'o' taq ruk'u'x na'oj achoq pa kiwi' nisamäj el wakami, richin ninuk' ri jaqäl k'amaya'l niqajo':


;Online Privacy & Security
Ichinan K'amab'ey & Jikomal


;People understand and can meaningfully control how their data is collected and used online, and trust that it’s safe. In parallel, companies and governments work to protect our data and enhance our ownership over our digital identities.
Ri winaqi' niq'ax pa kiwi' chuqa' nikichajij ütz ri rub'eyal yekik'öl ri taq tzij chuqa' nikokisaj pa k'amab'ey, chuqa' kikuqub'an kik'u'x chi e jikïl. Rachib'ilan chi ri taq ajk'aymoloj chuqa' ri chanpomanela' yesamäj richin yekichajij ri taq qatzij chuqa' nikib'än rutzil ri qichinem niqab'än pa kiwi' ri na'ob'alil taq b'anikil.


;Open Innovation
Jaqäl tz'ukuj


;Open is the default: open source and open standards continue to be at the heart of the Internet, and influence organizations and industries products, policies and practices. As a result, entrepreneurs and everyday Internet users can create, innovate and compete online without asking permission.
Jaqäl ja ri' ri retal ruk'amon wi pe: ri jaqäl chuqa' jikïl taq b'eyal k'a e k'o na pa ruk'u'x ri K'amaya'l, ri k'o nikib'än pa taq moloj chuqa' pa taq k'iyb'anoj, taq tikojil, taq na'ojil chuqa' taq samaj. Ri nuq'i' chi ri ajk'aymoloj chuqa' ri qawinaq pa K'amaya'l yetikïr nikinük', nikitz'ük chuqa' nikijunamaj ki' pa k'amab'ey, akuchi' man k'atzinel ta nikik'utuj q'ij.


;Decentralization
Jachsamajinem


;The technologies and platforms people use every day are interoperable and based on open standards. People expect and demand systems that allow seamless flow and transfer of information and content.
Ri taq na'ob'äl chuqa' taq nuk'uche'el yekokisaj q'ij q'ij ri winaqi' kan e kasamajib'el chuqa' enuk'un rik'in ri jaqäl taq b'eyal. Ri winaqi' yekoyob'ej chuqa' yekik'utuj taq q'inoj, ri nikiya' q'ij chi ke ri junelïk taq kib'enam chuqa' kiq'axik ri etamab'äl chuqa' rupam etamanïk.


;Web Literacy
Ajk'amaya'l tijoj


;People have the skills to read, write and participate in the digital world. Together, these informed digital citizens move beyond just consuming content, to creating, shaping and defending the web.
Ri winaqi' k'o ketaman yesik'in wuj, yetz'ib'an chuqa' yeto'on pa ri na'ob'alil ruwach'ulew. Pa kijunamil re na'ob'alil taq ajtinamït, ri ya'on rutzijol chi ke kan yeb'e näj richin yokikisaj ri taq rupam na'oj, nikitz'ük, nikib'än runuk'ulem chuqa' nikiköl ri Ajk'amaya'l.


;Digital Inclusion
Ajilal tz'aqat


;People everywhere can access and have the opportunity to participate in building the entire Internet. Subsequently, everyone on the Internet has the opportunity to access and shape our digital world. The Internet reflects the diversity of the people who use it.
Ri winaqi' xab'akuchi' nitikïr nok chuqa' nitikïr nito'on richin ninuk' ronojel ri K'amaya'l. Chi rij ri' chuqa' chijun ajruwach'ulew pa K'amaya'l nitikïr nok chuqa' nub'än rutzil ri na'ob'alil qaruwach'ulew. Ri K'amaya'l nuk'üt ri jalajoj kib'anikil winaqi' ye'okisan richin.


;Mozilla and our allies will bring these issues front-and-center by being an increasingly visible public voice, weaving these issues throughout our leadership and advocacy work, and building technologies that take a stance.
Mozilla chuqa' ri qato'onela' xkekinab'eyisaj re taq ruk'u'x na'oj re' ruma chi wkami nupo' pe ri achi'el ri tz'etel k'wayöl qatzij, rik'in kikemik re taq ruk'u'x na'oj re' chupam chijun ri qasamaj pa ruwi' poponem chuqa' kolonem, chuqa' kinuk'ik taq na'ob'alil ri k'o jikïl nikoqaj.


